['\n', <p><strong>Geo-Logix</strong> provides environmental and geotechnical engineering services to clients around Australia and is seeking an environmental scientist with
<strong>2 to 4 years' experience</strong> in environmental consulting to join our team.</p>, '\n', <p>The successful candidate will have experience in managing and completing contaminated land assessments and remediation projects and will be keen to expand their professional skills. You will have the opportunity to work with a close knit team of environmental
 scientists, geotech engineers and an accredited auditor in undertaking field and office based work.</p>, '\n', <p>The person we are looking for is:</p>, '\n', <ul>
<li>Highly motivated with the ability to engage with clients one on one; </li><li>Driven to develop expert-level technical and project management skills; </li><li>Quality minded with excellent attention to detail; and </li><li>Focused on delivering outstanding service to our clients.</li></ul>, '\n', <p><strong>Job responsibilities:</strong></p>, '\n', <ul>
<li>Perform contaminated land investigations and assessments individually and as part of a team;
</li><li>Assist and manage project planning and deliverables; </li><li>Interpret data, perform analysis, draw conclusions and make recommendations; </li><li>Prepare technical reports; </li><li>Maintain customer contact and liaison; </li><li>Prepare cost estimations for proposals; </li><li>Utilise project management software to monitor project timelines and budgets; and
</li><li>Provide audit support for contaminated land projects.</li></ul>, '\n', <p><strong>Job requirements:</strong></p>, '\n', <ul>
<li>Tertiary qualifications in a relevant earth science or civil or environmental engineering;
</li><li>Between 2 and 4 years' experience; </li><li>Knowledge and experience with soil, groundwater and vapour sampling methods and techniques;
</li><li>Comprehensive understanding of relevant legislation and guidelines related to contaminated land (including NEPM);
</li><li>Outstanding analytical and problem solving skills; </li><li>Excellent attention to detail particularly for data logging, data interpretation and preparation of reports;
</li><li>Excellent oral and written communication and ability to relate to colleagues and clients;
</li><li>Ability to work within a team to foster team cooperation and achievement; </li><li>A demonstrated commitment to work within a quality environment and maintain workplace safety standards;
</li><li>Driver's license (preferably manual) </li><li>Australian permanent resident</li></ul>, '\n', <p><strong>About Geo-Logix</strong></p>, '\n', <p>This is an exciting opportunity for personal and technical development in a growing consultancy business that was founded in 2005. Our core services include contamination investigations and assessments; site remediation and management; property due diligence;
 contaminated site audits and geotechnical engineering. We have an interesting and varied portfolio of projects that extends to emerging contaminants such as PFAS. Our services are provided to a broad range of private and government clients including some of
 Australia's biggest companies. The role will ensure opportunities to contribute to a range of projects involving both office and field based work mostly within NSW but also interstate.</p>, '\n', <p>Geo-Logix is located on Sydney's northern beaches. We offer a friendly and enjoyable working environment, on-going mentoring and professional development together with a performance scheme and attractive salary that will be negotiated in line with the skills
 and experience offered.</p>, '\n', <p>This position is available for an immediate start.  Please email your application and cover letter to Anita Tymkiw at
<strong>atymkiw@geo-logix.com.au</strong> by <strong>12 May 2017.</strong></p>, '\n']
